race.comment: ASK THE CAPTAIN (1) was very good at first two runs from a break then blew the start and not a lot went right last time. Wasn't beaten far but was below best figures. Given a fresh-up and looks well placed here. Worth another chance. PARERA (3) resumed with a good run and finished in front of ASK THE CAPTAIN when runner-up. In turn has also since run below best when stepping up to 1500m last time. Fresh for this and rates strongly on the previous run. VEOMAS (9) has had two starts and been well fancied in both stakes class on debut then richer company than this last time. Given another spell and gets chance to show wares this class. DANCING JUICE (2) is an eight start maiden who returns from a spell. Tested out to 2000m last time in but has run a couple of placings over shorter. Returns on the back of two trials and with the blinkers on. Trip should suit fresh.
